			<span class="uportal-channel-text">
                                        <newsContent>
                                            <br>The New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection (NJDEP) has awarded NJIT a $289,000 grant to investigate alternative measures for flood mitigation in the Hackensack/Moonachie/Little Ferry area.&nbsp; The effort will enhance rather than duplicate any on-going efforts by the US Army Corps of Engineers and other organizations.&nbsp; NJIT&rsquo;s newest center, the Flood Mitigation Engineering Resource Center will handle the work.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.njit.edu/news/2013/2013-291.php" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.njit.edu/features/uicomponents/images/next.gif" border="0"></a>
                                            <BR>
